# Coverage exclusions (ERE patterns matched against coverage.out lines).
#
# Convention:
#
#   1. Entry-point shims: `cmd/<binary>/main.go` excluded wholesale.
#      Keep main() to bare flag parsing, signal handling, and
#      dependency assembly. Anything testable belongs in internal/*
#      where it must be 100% covered. (pinoauth is a library and
#      currently ships no binaries — the pattern is kept for future
#      use.)
#
#   2. Structurally-unreachable defensive code: isolate it in a file
#      named `unreachable.go` inside the package that needs it. The
#      project-wide `/unreachable\.go:` pattern excludes the file.
#      Each helper in unreachable.go gets a doc comment justifying
#      why it cannot be reached from a test. When the unreachable
#      code is an error branch the production caller can't trigger,
#      the helper should `panic` rather than return the error — that
#      way the caller has no impossible `if err != nil` branch left
#      over to cover.
#
# Reference: slack-acp's AGENTS.md "Coverage" section
# (github.com/kfet/slack-acp).

^github.com/kfet/pinoauth/cmd/[^/]+/main\.go:
/unreachable\.go:
